==German==
{{wikipedia|lang=de}}
[[File:Seal Berlin 1253.png|right|thumb|The oldest seal of the city, from 1253, bears the inscription SIGILLVM DE BERLIN BVRGENSIS (Siegel der Bürger von Berlin).]]

===Alternative forms===
* {{l|de|Berl.}} {{qualifier|abbreviation}}

===Etymology===
Possibly from the {{etyl|pox|de}} stem {{m|pox|berl-}} / {{m|pox|birl-||swamp}} + suffix {{m|pox|-in}}. The place is first mentioned by this name in the late 12th century (as {{m|gml|Berlyn}}). According to (incorrect) [[folk etymology]], the name is derived from the {{m|de|Bär||bear}} that is the symbol of the city.

